    "name": "Mesh convergence study — non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model to quantify discretization error. Four mesh densities (coarse, medium, fine, extra-fine) were evaluated; element counts ranged from 18 400 to 312 000 hexahedral-dominant elements. The Richardson extrapolation procedure was applied to construct stiffness and yield force QoIs. Grid convergence index (GCI) values were computed for each refinement pair. The study concluded that the medium mesh (≈82 000 elements) achieved a GCI below 1.5% for all QoIs and was adopted for the validation ensemble runs.",
    "activityType": "MeshConvergenceStudy",
